The '''Addison-5 Representative District''' is a one member state [[Vermont Representative Districts, 2002-2012|Representative district]] in the [[United States|U.S.]] state of [[Vermont]].  It is one the 108 one or two member districts into which the state was divided by the [[redistricting]] and [[reapportionment]] plan developed by the [[Vermont General Assembly]] following the [[United States Census, 2000|2000 U.S. Census]].  The plan applies to legislatures elected in 2002, 2004, 2006, 2008, and 2010.  A new plan will be developed in 2012 following the [[2010 U.S. Census]].

The Addison-5 District includes all of the [[Addison County, Vermont|Addison County]] towns of  [[Bridport, Vermont|Bridport]], [[New Haven, Vermont|New Haven]], and [[Weybridge, Vermont|Weybridge]].

As of the 2000 census, the state as a whole had a population of 608,827. As there are a total of 150 representatives, there were 4,059 residents per representative (or 8,118 residents per two representatives). The one member Addison-5 District had a population of 3,725 in that same census, 8.23% below the state average.

